Source: thaifonts-scalable
Section: x11
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Chanop Silpa-Anan <chanop@debian.org>
Build-Depends-Indep: debhelper (>> 4.0.0), defoma (>= 0.7.0), fontforge|pfaedit, po-debconf, xfonts-utils|xutils|ttmkfdir
Standards-Version: 3.6.2.2

Package: t1-thai-tlwg
Architecture: all
Depends: defoma
Description: Thai fonts in Type1 format
 This package provides some public domain fonts that are
 enhanced by developpers from Thai Linux Working Group.
 In Type1 format.
 .
 At the moment there are three families from the National Font
 Project included here:
  - Garuda
  - Norasi
 and three developed by TLWG itself:
  - Tlwg Mono
  - Tlwg Typewriter
  - Purisa

Package: ttf-thai-tlwg
Architecture: all
Depends: po-debconf, defoma, x-ttcidfont-conf
Replaces: xfonts-thai-ttf
Description: Thai fonts in TrueType format
 This package provides some public domain fonts that are
 enhanced by developpers from Thai Linux Working Group.
 In Type1 format.
 .
 At the moment there are three families from the National Font
 Project included here:
  - Garuda
  - Norasi
 and three developed by TLWG itself:
  - Tlwg Mono
  - Tlwg Typewriter
  - Purisa

